data.description: Welcome home! Where the magic of nature and architecture meet! This stunning property boasts of not only 14 pecan trees, a pomegranate tree, fig tree and multiple berry trees and vines but also features crepe myrtles, four o'clock lilies, daffodils, irises, yucca palms and wisteria. As a Southern paradise for gardeners and landscapers, the soil is exceptionally fertile due to the natural cycle of pecan mulch added over the years. Relax in the 6-person hot tub, entertain guests on the large front porch, or have a BBQ on the spacious deck in the back. Investors could benefit from a short term rental with this huge and welcoming home! Richland Chambers Lake is less than 5 minutes away for the avid or weekend angler. The 2-story treehouse is perfect for kids to explore while you enjoy the stunning view of your 1.17-acre corner lot yard. Kerens schools are in walking distance. The original architect's plans and bill of sale for materials are available making this an exceptional piece of history.  Water well in the backyard available for landscape needs. This home boasts of a large attic and plenty of storage under the staircase. Enjoy the sunroom with large windows surrounding you and a separate entry to the back deck.  Original wooden staircase with a landing and architecturally stunning banisters creating a gorgeous entry view. Beautiful original French doors to the formal dining room. Snuggle up with a book in the cozy and spacious window seat bench. Vintage and original fixtures throughout. Fireplaces to warm up to in the living room and the primary bedroom. Don't miss this opportunity to witness the serenity of this property for yourself. Come and see it firsthand. Scheduled your appointment today! 903-312-6338
